      "value": "<p>&gt;@UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.hIhgdXnqGHBm0A64]{Envoy Improvisation}</p>\n<p>Not only are you ready to risk yourself to protect others—your sacrifice also inspires your companion. You gain @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.feats.1auTCZ8OB64XqXcZ]{Bodyguard} as a bonus feat. If you already have Bodyguard, you instead gain @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.feats.zOvuXKOIFXBJIMT6]{In Harm’s Way} as a bonus feat. If you use In Harm’s Way to intercept an attack that then reduces you to 0 Hit Points, you grant the attack’s original target a +1 morale bonus to AC, attack rolls, saving throws, and skill checks, as well as a number of temporary Hit Points equal to [[@classes.envoy.levels+@abilities.cha.mod]]{your envoy level + your Charisma modifier}. These benefits last for a number of rounds equal to [[@abilities.cha.mod]]{your Charisma modifier} or until you regain consciousness, whichever happens first.</p>"
